@page "/how-to-play"

<PageTitle>How to Play - Blackjack</PageTitle>

<div class="how-to-play">
    <h1>📖 How to Play Blackjack</h1>

    <div class="panel mt-2">
        <h2>🎯 Objective</h2>
        <p class="mt-1">Beat the dealer by getting a hand total closer to <strong>21</strong> than the dealer — without going over (busting). You play only against the dealer, not other players.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="panel mt-2">
        <h2>🃏 Card Values</h2>
        <ul class="rules-list mt-1">
            <li><strong>Number cards (2–10)</strong> — Worth their face value.</li>
            <li><strong>Face cards (Jack, Queen, King)</strong> — Worth 10 points each.</li>
            <li><strong>Ace</strong> — Worth 11 points, or 1 point if 11 would cause a bust.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="panel mt-2">
        <h2>🎮 Gameplay</h2>
        <ol class="rules-list mt-1">
            <li>Place your <strong>bet</strong> using the chip buttons before each round.</li>
            <li>You and the dealer are each dealt <strong>two cards</strong>. One of the dealer's cards is face down.</li>
            <li>Choose your action:
                <ul class="rules-list mt-1">
                    <li><strong>Hit</strong> — Take another card to increase your total.</li>
                    <li><strong>Stand</strong> — Keep your current hand and end your turn.</li>
                    <li><strong>Double Down</strong> — Double your bet and receive exactly one more card.</li>
                    <li><strong>Split</strong> — If your first two cards have the same value, split them into two separate hands, each with its own bet.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>The dealer then reveals their hidden card and must <strong>hit until reaching 17 or higher</strong>.</li>
            <li>The hand closest to 21 without busting wins.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="panel mt-2">
        <h2>💰 Payouts</h2>
        <ul class="rules-list mt-1">
            <li><strong>Win</strong> — You receive your bet back plus an equal amount.</li>
            <li><strong>Blackjack</strong> (Ace + 10-value card on the initial deal) — Pays <strong>3:2</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>Push</strong> (tie with the dealer) — Your original bet is returned.</li>
            <li><strong>Bust or dealer wins</strong> — You lose your bet.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="panel mt-2">
        <h2>⚡ Key Terms</h2>
        <ul class="rules-list mt-1">
            <li><strong>Blackjack</strong> — An Ace plus any 10-value card dealt as the first two cards.</li>
            <li><strong>Bust</strong> — A hand total that exceeds 21; an automatic loss.</li>
            <li><strong>Soft hand</strong> — A hand containing an Ace counted as 11.</li>
            <li><strong>Hard hand</strong> — A hand with no Ace, or where the Ace is counted as 1.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-3">
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">🎰 Start Playing!</a>
    </div>
</div>
